class Solution {
public:
    string reverseWords(string s) {
        int start = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i <= s.size(); i++) {
            if (i == s.size() || s[i] == ' ') {
                reverse(s.begin() + start, s.begin() + i);
                start = i + 1;
            }
        }
        return s;
    }
};
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Reversing each word in-place by identifying word boundaries and using the `reverse` function from the C++ Standard Library.
